OL,3,CKeir Starmer massively shrinks
OL,4,CLabour's green investments
OL,6,FLabour has dropped its pledge to spend
OL,7,F#28 billion a year on environmental
OL,8,Fprojects, Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,9,Fconfirmed, in a major U-turn by the
OL,10,Fparty, ITV News Political Editor
OL,11,FRobert Peston reports
OL,13,Fhasn't just ditched his promise to
OL,14,Fspend #28 billion a year on green
OL,15,Finvestment, he has shrunk it as though
OL,16,Fit was put through the hottest wash.
OL,17,FTo choose a possibly jarring metaphor,
OL,18,Ffashionable super baggy jeans have
OL,19,Fbecome tiny hot pants.
