OL,3,CKeir Starmer massively shrinks
OL,4,CLabour's green investments
OL,6,FEven so, this is a massive cut, and
OL,7,Fthe economic context is that
OL,8,Finvestment in the UK has been below
OL,9,Finternational norms for decades. Also,
OL,10,Fthe ravages of inflation mean public
OL,11,Fsector investment was set to fall as a
OL,12,Fshare of GDP even if Labour had stuck
OL,13,Fwith its #28 billion.
OL,15,FStarmer's explanation and
OL,16,Fjustification is that the public
OL,17,Fsector finances have deteriorated
OL,18,Fsince Reeves first made the #28
OL,19,Fbillion commitment in September 2021.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/10
