OL,3,CKeir Starmer massively shrinks
OL,4,CLabour's green investments
OL,6,FThey believed that what may be lost
OL,7,Fthrough less public investment will be
OL,8,Fmade up by massive easing of planning
OL,9,Fconstraints and aligning regulation
OL,10,Fmore closely with supplier and
OL,11,Finvestor requirements, to unlock
OL,12,Fprivate investment.
OL,14,FIn essence they will be riding more
OL,15,Froughshod over nimbies and allowing
OL,16,Fthe private sector more certainty over
OL,17,Frevenue flows. Which is likely to be
OL,18,Feffective, though neither is without
OL,19,Fcontroversy, especially on the left of
OL,20,Ftheir party.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/10
